Class CarlSortedList<T extends java.lang.Comparable<? super T>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • CarlSortedList<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - The type of data that the list stores.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<T>, SortedList<T>

    public class CarlSortedList<T extends java.lang.Comparable<? super T>>
extends java.lang.Object
implements SortedList<T>
    An implementation of the SortedList ADT. Note that you cannot add null items to a sorted list, since the list must be able to compare the values of items.
